function [C]=exponentialC(D,param);% exponentialC              - exponential covariance model (Jan 1,2001)%% Compute the exponential covariance matrix from a distance matrix.% % SYNTAX :%% [C]=exponentialC(D,param);%% INPUT :%% D       n by m   distance matrix, having real values >=0.% param   1 by 2   vector of parameters such that param(1) is the sill%                  and param(2) is the range of the model (i.e. the%                  distance to reach 5% of the sill value).%% OUTPUT :%% C       n by m   covariance matrix with same size as D.C=param(1)*exp(-3*D/param(2));